README.md
     9вҶ’# Mitt
    11вҶ’> Tiny 200b functional event emitter / pubsub.
    12вҶ’
    13вҶ’-   **Microscopic:** weighs less than 200 bytes gzipped
    14вҶ’-   **Useful:** a wildcard `"*"` event type listens to all events
    15вҶ’-   **Familiar:** same names & ideas as [Node's EventEmitter](https://nodejs.org/api/events.html#events_class_eventemitter)
    16вҶ’-   **Functional:** methods don't rely on `this`
    17вҶ’-   **Great Name:** somehow [mitt](https://npm.im/mitt) wasn't taken
    18вҶ’
    19вҶ’Mitt was made for the browser, but works in any JavaScript runtime. It has no dependencies and supports IE9+.
    20вҶ’
    21вҶ’## Table of Contents
    23вҶ’-   [Install](#install)
    24вҶ’-   [Usage](#usage)
    25вҶ’-   [Examples & Demos](#examples--demos)
    26вҶ’-   [API](#api)
    27вҶ’-   [Contribute](#contribute)
    28вҶ’-   [License](#license)
    29вҶ’
    30вҶ’## Install
    32вҶ’This project uses [node](http://nodejs.org) and [npm](https://npmjs.com). Go check them out if you don't have them locally installed.
    33вҶ’
    34вҶ’```sh
    35вҶ’$ npm install --save mitt
    36вҶ’```
    37вҶ’
    38вҶ’Then with a module bundler like [rollup](http://rollupjs.org/) or [webpack](https://webpack.js.org/), use as you would anything else:
    39вҶ’
    40вҶ’```javascript
    41вҶ’// using ES6 modules
    42вҶ’import mitt from 'mitt'
    43вҶ’
    44вҶ’// using CommonJS modules
    45вҶ’var mitt = require('mitt')
    46вҶ’```
    47вҶ’
    48вҶ’The [UMD](https://github.com/umdjs/umd) build is also available on [unpkg](https://unpkg.com):
    49вҶ’
    50вҶ’```html
    51вҶ’<script src="https://unpkg.com/mitt/dist/mitt.umd.js"></script>
    52вҶ’```
    53вҶ’
    54вҶ’You can find the library on `window.mitt`.
    55вҶ’
    56вҶ’## Usage
    58вҶ’```js
    59вҶ’import mitt from 'mitt'
    60вҶ’
    61вҶ’const emitter = mitt()
    62вҶ’
    63вҶ’// listen to an event
    64вҶ’emitter.on('foo', e => console.log('foo', e) )
    65вҶ’
    66вҶ’// listen to all events
    67вҶ’emitter.on('*', (type, e) => console.log(type, e) )
    68вҶ’
    69вҶ’// fire an event
    70вҶ’emitter.emit('foo', { a: 'b' })
    71вҶ’
    72вҶ’// clearing all events
    73вҶ’emitter.all.clear()
    74вҶ’
    75вҶ’// working with handler references:
    76вҶ’function onFoo() {}
    77вҶ’emitter.on('foo', onFoo)   // listen
    78вҶ’emitter.off('foo', onFoo)  // unlisten
    79вҶ’```
    80вҶ’
    81вҶ’### Typescript
    83вҶ’Set `"strict": true` in your tsconfig.json to get improved type inference for `mitt` instance methods.
    84вҶ’
    85вҶ’```ts
    86вҶ’import mitt from 'mitt';
    87вҶ’
    88вҶ’type Events = {
    89вҶ’  foo: string;
    90вҶ’  bar?: number;
    91вҶ’};
    92вҶ’
