   135вҶ’-   [emit](#emit)
   136вҶ’    -   [Parameters](#parameters-2)
   137вҶ’
   138вҶ’### mitt
   140вҶ’Mitt: Tiny (~200b) functional event emitter / pubsub.
   141вҶ’
   142вҶ’Returns **Mitt** 
   143вҶ’
   144вҶ’### all
   146вҶ’A Map of event names to registered handler functions.
   147вҶ’
   148вҶ’### on
   150вҶ’Register an event handler for the given type.
   151вҶ’
   152вҶ’#### Parameters
   154вҶ’-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to listen for, or `'*'` for all events
   155вҶ’-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** Function to call in response to given event
   156вҶ’
   157вҶ’### off
   159вҶ’Remove an event handler for the given type.
   160вҶ’If `handler` is omitted, all handlers of the given type are removed.
   161вҶ’
   162вҶ’#### Parameters
   164вҶ’-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to unregister `handler` from, or `'*'`
   165вҶ’-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)?** Handler function to remove
   166вҶ’
   167вҶ’### emit
   169вҶ’Invoke all handlers for the given type.
   170вҶ’If present, `'*'` handlers are invoked after type-matched handlers.
   171вҶ’
   172вҶ’Note: Manually firing '\*' handlers is not supported.
   173вҶ’
   174вҶ’#### Parameters
   176вҶ’-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** The event type to invoke
   177вҶ’-   `evt` **Any?** Any value (object is recommended and powerful), passed to each handler
   178вҶ’
   179вҶ’## Contribute
   181вҶ’First off, thanks for taking the time to contribute!
   182вҶ’Now, take a moment to be sure your contributions make sense to everyone else.
   183вҶ’
   184вҶ’### Reporting Issues
   186вҶ’Found a problem? Want a new feature? First of all see if your issue or idea has [already been reported](../../issues).
   187вҶ’If don't, just open a [new clear and descriptive issue](../../issues/new).
   188вҶ’
   189вҶ’### Submitting pull requests
   191вҶ’Pull requests are the greatest contributions, so be sure they are focused in scope, and do avoid unrelated commits.
   192вҶ’
   193вҶ’-   Fork it!
   194вҶ’-   Clone your fork: `git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/mitt`
   195вҶ’-   Navigate to the newly cloned directory: `cd mitt`
   196вҶ’-   Create a new branch for the new feature: `git checkout -b my-new-feature`
   197вҶ’-   Install the tools necessary for development: `npm install`
   198вҶ’-   Make your changes.
   199вҶ’-   Commit your changes: `git commit -am 'Add some feature'`
   200вҶ’-   Push to the branch: `git push origin my-new-feature`
